2. Interpretation
In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires—
"authorised officer" means an officer of the Registrar authorised by the Registrar to perform duties under this Act;
"ammunition" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Arms and Ammunition Act (Cap. 24:01);
"arms" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Arms and Ammunition Act;
"competent authority" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Financial Intelligence Act (Cap. 08:07);
[ 5 of 2025, s. 2. ]
"Council" means the Advisory and Arbitration Council established under section 21;
"day" means any day other than a Saturday, Sunday or any day which is a public holiday under the Public Holidays Act;
[ 5 of 2025, s. 2. ]
"financial offence" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Financial Intelligence Act (Cap. 08:07);
"formation" means first meeting of the proposed society for the drafting of the constitution after name reservation;
[ 5 of 2025, s. 2. ]
"illegal society" means a society in terms of section 5(7) that operates without a certificate of registration of approval issued by the Registrar of societies;
"illicit dealing in arms or ammunition" means a contravention of any of the provisions of Parts IV to VI of the Arms and Ammunition Act;
"money laundering" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Proceeds and Instruments of Crime Act (Cap. 08:03);
"office-bearer" of a society means any elected, appointed or co-opted person who is a member of the board, committee or governing body thereof;
"premises" means a place of operation and or an administrative office of the society;
[ 5 of 2025, s. 2. ]
"proliferation" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Counter Terrorism Act (Cap. 08:08);
"proposed society" means any club, company, partnership political party or association of 20 or more persons, whatever its nature or objects, or any association of 20 or more persons, for a religious society who have submitted their intentions to register a society;
[ 5 of 2025, s. 2. ]
"register" means a register of societies that is kept and maintained by the Registrar under section 8;
"Registrar" means the Registrar of Societies appointed under section 3;
"society" means—
( a ) any club, company, partnership or association of 20 or more persons, whatever its nature or objects, or any association of 20 or more persons, for a religious society, but does not include—
(i) any company as defined by the Companies Act (Cap. 42:01), or any company to which Part VII of that Act applies which has complied with the requirements of section 285 of that Act;
(ii) any company or association constituted under any written law for the time being in force in Botswana;
(iii) any trade union, federation of trade unions or employers' organisation registered under the Trade Unions and Employers' Organisations Act (Cap. 48:01),
(iv) any company, association or partnership consisting of not more than 20 persons, formed for the sole purpose of carrying on any lawful business,
(v) any co-operative society, registered under the Co-operative Societies Act (Cap. 42:04),
(vi) any board of governors, local education authority, school committee or similar organization established under Education Act (Cap. 58:01),
(vii) any building society registered under the Building Societies Act (Cap. 42:03); or
(viii) any society or class of society which may be declared not to be a society for the purposes of this Act; or
( b ) a political party of 20 or more persons listed in the Schedule.
[ 5 of 2025, s. 2. ]
"terrorism" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Counter-Terrorism Act (Cap. 08:08); and
[ 5 of 2025, s. 2. ]
"terrorism financing" has the same meaning assigned to it under the Counter-Terrorism Act.
[ 5 of 2025, s. 2. ]
(2) Where a body of persons, whether corporate or unincorporated is a member of an association, all members of such body shall be deemed to be members of such association.
